This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it addresses the task of unsupervised Semantic Textual Similarity (STS) using pre-trained sentence encoders. It also applies and extends different meta-embedding methods from the word embedding literature, which is a common technique in NLP research. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves ensembling diverse pre-trained models and using different meta-embedding methods to improve performance. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves developing a system that can understand and compare the meaning of natural language sentences. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the task of STS involves finding similar sentences based on their semantic meaning. 

Finally, Computer Vision (cs.CV) could also be a relevant sub-category as the paper uses techniques such as dimensionality reduction and autoencoders, which are commonly used in image processing and computer vision research.
